  "questions": [
    {
      "text": "A 2500-g (5-lb 8-oz) healthy male newborn delivered at 38 weeks' gestation after an uncomplicated pregnancy undergoes circumcision 48 hours after birth. The procedure is uncomplicated. Three hours after the procedure, the mother reports that the newborn is not feeding well and cries and coughs often. His temperature is 36.6°C (98.0°F), pulse is 170/min, respirations are 62/min, and blood pressure is 80/50 mm Hg. Pulse oximetry on room air shows an oxygen saturation of 100%. The neonate intermittently clenches his hands and toes, opens his mouth, and tightly closes his eyes. Muscle tone in the extremities is increased. The diaper is wet with clear urine and traces of blood. Examination of the genitalia shows a crust of blood along the cut prepuce, erythema of the glans penis, and edema around the corona of the glans penis. Lungs are clear to auscultation. Heart sounds are normal. Which of the following is the most appropriate next step in management?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Topical lidocaine therapy"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Noninvasive ventilation therapy"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Reassurance"
        },
        {
          "id": 4,
          "text": "Intravenous ketamine therapy"
        },
        {
          "id": 5,
          "text": "Oral flucloxacillin therapy"
        },
        {
          "id": 6,
          "text": "Urinary catheterization"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 1,
      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) CORRECT:</h4>In a <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=a40Q3T&anker=Z6f0fa51eb81a7d03aa179eab82aacab8\" data-learningcard-id=\"a40Q3T\" data-anker=\"Z6f0fa51eb81a7d03aa179eab82aacab8\" data-sememe-id=\"-m0DRg\">neonate</a> with signs and symptoms that suggest <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xN0EWg&anker=Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-learningcard-id=\"xN0EWg\" data-anker=\"Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-section-id=\"NBX-a00\">pain</a> following an invasive procedure, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xN0EWg&anker=Z937eb02dfdae5d3235cea8d72ffaf83f\" data-learningcard-id=\"xN0EWg\" data-anker=\"Z937eb02dfdae5d3235cea8d72ffaf83f\" data-section-id=\"5BXiY00\" data-sememe-id=\"CWbqns\">analgesia</a> with a combination of <span class=\"wichtig\"><b>pharmacological and nonpharmacological measures</b></span> is indicated. The initial choice of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xN0EWg&anker=Z937eb02dfdae5d3235cea8d72ffaf83f\" data-learningcard-id=\"xN0EWg\" data-anker=\"Z937eb02dfdae5d3235cea8d72ffaf83f\" data-section-id=\"5BXiY00\" data-sememe-id=\"CWbqns\">analgesic</a> intervention depends on the anticipated intensity of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xN0EWg&anker=Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-learningcard-id=\"xN0EWg\" data-anker=\"Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-section-id=\"NBX-a00\">pain</a>. First-line pharmacological therapy in a <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=a40Q3T&anker=Z6f0fa51eb81a7d03aa179eab82aacab8\" data-learningcard-id=\"a40Q3T\" data-anker=\"Z6f0fa51eb81a7d03aa179eab82aacab8\" data-sememe-id=\"-m0DRg\">neonate</a> with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xN0EWg&anker=Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-learningcard-id=\"xN0EWg\" data-anker=\"Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-section-id=\"NBX-a00\">pain</a> following <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=rF0fj3&anker=Z67ce853a61229ff007038c97630cd26d\" data-learningcard-id=\"rF0fj3\" data-anker=\"Z67ce853a61229ff007038c97630cd26d\" data-sememe-id=\"6V1jvf0\">circumcision</a> is <span class=\"wichtig\"><b>topical <span data-sememe-id=\"hj1cZS0\">anesthetics</span></b></span> (e.g., topical <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=wN0hWg&anker=Z4e597a5573ddee2b3c1f06b0d0ceb97a\" data-learningcard-id=\"wN0hWg\" data-anker=\"Z4e597a5573ddee2b3c1f06b0d0ceb97a\" data-section-id=\"U7bbOE\" data-sememe-id=\"1ia2q4\">lidocaine</a>). If the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=a40Q3T&anker=Z6f0fa51eb81a7d03aa179eab82aacab8\" data-learningcard-id=\"a40Q3T\" data-anker=\"Z6f0fa51eb81a7d03aa179eab82aacab8\" data-sememe-id=\"-m0DRg\">neonate</a> still shows signs and symptoms of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xN0EWg&anker=Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-learningcard-id=\"xN0EWg\" data-anker=\"Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-section-id=\"NBX-a00\">pain</a> despite topical therapy, other therapies should be considered following a stepwise approach (i.e., systemic <span class=\"wichtig\"><b><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=BN0zWg&anker=Za3da7a7c0e6eb1d1d781615b1c2c7af3\" data-learningcard-id=\"BN0zWg\" data-anker=\"Za3da7a7c0e6eb1d1d781615b1c2c7af3\" data-section-id=\"Ykcnmc0\" data-sememe-id=\"gvYFzI\">acetaminophen</a> or <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=BN0zWg&anker=Z6d53b6cfe3376a70645a5c797293e56a\" data-learningcard-id=\"BN0zWg\" data-anker=\"Z6d53b6cfe3376a70645a5c797293e56a\" data-section-id=\"0kcemc0\" data-sememe-id=\"riafG4\">NSAIDs</a></b></span> → intravenous <span class=\"wichtig\"><b><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=yN0ddg&anker=Z434daecbc44532c03b0313928f0c321d\" data-learningcard-id=\"yN0ddg\" data-anker=\"Z434daecbc44532c03b0313928f0c321d\" data-sememe-id=\"Ycbnas\">opioids</a> </b></span>→ <span class=\"wichtig\"><b>subcutaneous <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=wN0hWg&anker=Z4e597a5573ddee2b3c1f06b0d0ceb97a\" data-learningcard-id=\"wN0hWg\" data-anker=\"Z4e597a5573ddee2b3c1f06b0d0ceb97a\" data-section-id=\"U7bbOE\" data-sememe-id=\"1ia2q4\">lidocaine</a>/specific <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Sl0ywT&anker=Z005a641786ea9ef3d6131d6b9c8262ea\" data-learningcard-id=\"Sl0ywT\" data-anker=\"Z005a641786ea9ef3d6131d6b9c8262ea\" data-section-id=\"pNcLX10\" data-sememe-id=\"53biQt\">nerve blocks</a></b></span> → <span class=\"wichtig\"><b>sedation</b></span>). In addition, nonpharmacological measures, such as <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=N80-53&anker=Zbe09275ed15b7d7474f31701b5b93428\" data-learningcard-id=\"N80-53\" data-anker=\"Zbe09275ed15b7d7474f31701b5b93428\" data-section-id=\"a-WQDL0\">breastfeeding</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=W60PPS&anker=Z84ffaf83e57bb0cc8eb7c50bbc266078\" data-learningcard-id=\"W60PPS\" data-anker=\"Z84ffaf83e57bb0cc8eb7c50bbc266078\">skin</a>-to-<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=W60PPS&anker=Z84ffaf83e57bb0cc8eb7c50bbc266078\" data-learningcard-id=\"W60PPS\" data-anker=\"Z84ffaf83e57bb0cc8eb7c50bbc266078\">skin</a> contact, and oral sucrose, are always indicated for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xN0EWg&anker=Z04036123bf992e2ea414321b2a6f5cbd\" data-learningcard-id=\"xN0EWg\" data-anker=\"Z04036123bf992e2ea414321b2a6f5cbd\">pain management</a>.<br><br>Although it was previously thought that <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=a40Q3T&anker=Z6f0fa51eb81a7d03aa179eab82aacab8\" data-learningcard-id=\"a40Q3T\" data-anker=\"Z6f0fa51eb81a7d03aa179eab82aacab8\" data-sememe-id=\"-m0DRg\">neonates</a> do not feel painful stimuli to the same degree as adults, accumulating evidence suggests otherwise. The sensory system is fully functional by the middle of the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=dO0orT&anker=Zf0f2ff7ad278432e44b34740976c7aca\" data-learningcard-id=\"dO0orT\" data-anker=\"Zf0f2ff7ad278432e44b34740976c7aca\" data-section-id=\"3I1ScR0\" data-sememe-id=\"GMcBJ10\">second trimester</a> and both preterm and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=a40Q3T&anker=Z943a0898a1066aee0aa86ab106da033e\" data-learningcard-id=\"a40Q3T\" data-anker=\"Z943a0898a1066aee0aa86ab106da033e\" data-section-id=\"_8X56-\" data-sememe-id=\"tDaXT5\">full-term</a> <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=a40Q3T&anker=Z6f0fa51eb81a7d03aa179eab82aacab8\" data-learningcard-id=\"a40Q3T\" data-anker=\"Z6f0fa51eb81a7d03aa179eab82aacab8\" data-sememe-id=\"-m0DRg\">neonates</a> experience painful stimuli. Following invasive procedures such as <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=rF0fj3&anker=Z67ce853a61229ff007038c97630cd26d\" data-learningcard-id=\"rF0fj3\" data-anker=\"Z67ce853a61229ff007038c97630cd26d\" data-sememe-id=\"6V1jvf0\">circumcision</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=a40Q3T&anker=Z6f0fa51eb81a7d03aa179eab82aacab8\" data-learningcard-id=\"a40Q3T\" data-anker=\"Z6f0fa51eb81a7d03aa179eab82aacab8\" data-sememe-id=\"-m0DRg\">neonates</a> should be assessed for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xN0EWg&anker=Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-learningcard-id=\"xN0EWg\" data-anker=\"Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-section-id=\"NBX-a00\">pain</a> and treated accordingly.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) INCORRECT:</h4>Noninvasive ventilation therapy is often indicated in <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=a40Q3T&anker=Z6f0fa51eb81a7d03aa179eab82aacab8\" data-learningcard-id=\"a40Q3T\" data-anker=\"Z6f0fa51eb81a7d03aa179eab82aacab8\" data-sememe-id=\"-m0DRg\">neonates</a> presenting with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=tH0XHh&anker=Z33ef7cab5ec891b82794259be7e75d5d\" data-learningcard-id=\"tH0XHh\" data-anker=\"Z33ef7cab5ec891b82794259be7e75d5d\" data-section-id=\"Q-1uCj0\">respiratory distress</a>. This patient, however, has no abnormal findings on cardiopulmonary examination and no signs of increased breathing effort (e.g., nasal flaring, intercostal retractions), <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=tl0XAT&anker=Z1f3675f255288bdb07d13ae3106fdf22\" data-learningcard-id=\"tl0XAT\" data-anker=\"Z1f3675f255288bdb07d13ae3106fdf22\" data-section-id=\"sCXttZ0\" data-sememe-id=\"yh0dgf\">cyanosis</a>, or <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ZI0ZYh&anker=Z11178ec3c2e582d07f19c0f784e018a3\" data-learningcard-id=\"ZI0ZYh\" data-anker=\"Z11178ec3c2e582d07f19c0f784e018a3\" data-section-id=\"5h1ieg0\" data-sememe-id=\"GT0BH2\">hypoxia</a> (normal <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=EJ08DS&anker=Zcdfc30b72bdf1b54bf2c4a1b18b109c4\" data-learningcard-id=\"EJ08DS\" data-anker=\"Zcdfc30b72bdf1b54bf2c4a1b18b109c4\" data-section-id=\"2X1Tx20\" data-sememe-id=\"UlXbwy\">oxygen saturation</a>). Crying babies often <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=3L0Sxg&anker=Z53178f74af701c6933574f4f111d6391\" data-learningcard-id=\"3L0Sxg\" data-anker=\"Z53178f74af701c6933574f4f111d6391\">cough</a> to clear the secretions that accumulate while crying; therefore, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=3L0Sxg&anker=Z53178f74af701c6933574f4f111d6391\" data-learningcard-id=\"3L0Sxg\" data-anker=\"Z53178f74af701c6933574f4f111d6391\">cough</a> is not considered a sign of disease here. <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=tl0XAT&anker=Z9f745914c0340ad3beed72e989c555ff\" data-learningcard-id=\"tl0XAT\" data-anker=\"Z9f745914c0340ad3beed72e989c555ff\" data-section-id=\"sCXttZ0\" data-sememe-id=\"Jj0sYT\">Tachypnea</a> and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=rM0fJg&anker=Z3ae4e1e5581c7405590e65b57fa82021\" data-learningcard-id=\"rM0fJg\" data-anker=\"Z3ae4e1e5581c7405590e65b57fa82021\" data-section-id=\"KVcUvY0\" data-sememe-id=\"lNbvY8\">tachycardia</a> are common responses to <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xN0EWg&anker=Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-learningcard-id=\"xN0EWg\" data-anker=\"Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-section-id=\"NBX-a00\">pain</a>; they are even included in certain scales and scores for <span data-sememe-id=\"RM1loh0\">neonatal pain assessment</span> (e.g., <span data-sememe-id=\"b-WHDL0\">NIPS</span>, CRIES).</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) INCORRECT:</h4>This <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=a40Q3T&anker=Z6f0fa51eb81a7d03aa179eab82aacab8\" data-learningcard-id=\"a40Q3T\" data-anker=\"Z6f0fa51eb81a7d03aa179eab82aacab8\" data-sememe-id=\"-m0DRg\">neonate</a> presents with signs and symptoms of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xN0EWg&anker=Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-learningcard-id=\"xN0EWg\" data-anker=\"Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-section-id=\"NBX-a00\">pain</a>, which need to be addressed. Untreated or poorly treated neonatal <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xN0EWg&anker=Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-learningcard-id=\"xN0EWg\" data-anker=\"Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-section-id=\"NBX-a00\">pain</a> has been associated with hypersensitivity to painful stimuli and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xN0EWg&anker=Z35660e26de3816a10472b57a663c874c\" data-learningcard-id=\"xN0EWg\" data-anker=\"Z35660e26de3816a10472b57a663c874c\" data-section-id=\"NBX-a00\" data-sememe-id=\"vpdArI0\">chronic pain</a> syndromes later in life. Reassurance alone is therefore not sufficient to manage this patient's <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xN0EWg&anker=Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-learningcard-id=\"xN0EWg\" data-anker=\"Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-section-id=\"NBX-a00\">pain</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) INCORRECT:</h4>Although this <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=a40Q3T&anker=Z6f0fa51eb81a7d03aa179eab82aacab8\" data-learningcard-id=\"a40Q3T\" data-anker=\"Z6f0fa51eb81a7d03aa179eab82aacab8\" data-sememe-id=\"-m0DRg\">neonate</a> presents with signs and symptoms that suggest <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xN0EWg&anker=Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-learningcard-id=\"xN0EWg\" data-anker=\"Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-section-id=\"NBX-a00\">pain</a>, which needs to be addressed, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=vN0A1g&anker=Za78fe43cf670dce14145938e200afce4\" data-learningcard-id=\"vN0A1g\" data-anker=\"Za78fe43cf670dce14145938e200afce4\" data-section-id=\"3PcSec0\" data-sememe-id=\"FRagK4\">ketamine</a>, administered for either <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xN0EWg&anker=Z937eb02dfdae5d3235cea8d72ffaf83f\" data-learningcard-id=\"xN0EWg\" data-anker=\"Z937eb02dfdae5d3235cea8d72ffaf83f\" data-section-id=\"5BXiY00\" data-sememe-id=\"CWbqns\">analgesia</a> or sedation, is not usually the first-line therapy in the treatment of postoperative <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xN0EWg&anker=Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-learningcard-id=\"xN0EWg\" data-anker=\"Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-section-id=\"NBX-a00\">pain</a> following <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=rF0fj3&anker=Z67ce853a61229ff007038c97630cd26d\" data-learningcard-id=\"rF0fj3\" data-anker=\"Z67ce853a61229ff007038c97630cd26d\" data-sememe-id=\"6V1jvf0\">circumcision</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>E) INCORRECT:</h4>Oral <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Z440d11d6f3ff6c4fa3129205ab64dd8a\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Z440d11d6f3ff6c4fa3129205ab64dd8a\" data-section-id=\"jRc_5X0\" data-sememe-id=\"AbbRwH\">flucloxacillin</a> therapy can be used to empirically treat postoperative infection following <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=rF0fj3&anker=Z67ce853a61229ff007038c97630cd26d\" data-learningcard-id=\"rF0fj3\" data-anker=\"Z67ce853a61229ff007038c97630cd26d\" data-sememe-id=\"6V1jvf0\">circumcision</a>. This patient, however, has no signs that suggest infection (e.g., drainage from the wound, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=j50_Pg&anker=Za5de83449ff6a749e6c1348b93b1f3b1\" data-learningcard-id=\"j50_Pg\" data-anker=\"Za5de83449ff6a749e6c1348b93b1f3b1\" data-sememe-id=\"CL0q-g\">fever</a>); <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_405NT&anker=Z2402afe504766ef84f64acad4aaea47b\" data-learningcard-id=\"_405NT\" data-anker=\"Z2402afe504766ef84f64acad4aaea47b\" data-section-id=\"0vXeA-\" data-sememe-id=\"3wYSir\">erythema</a> and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=SM0yLg&anker=Zc00dca4994157e86d8e6e8ee9510443f\" data-learningcard-id=\"SM0yLg\" data-anker=\"Zc00dca4994157e86d8e6e8ee9510443f\" data-section-id=\"JcXsWC\" data-sememe-id=\"Oo0IXS\">edema</a> of the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=l60vOS&anker=Z30a31b111175e0ac68095e551b8056af\" data-learningcard-id=\"l60vOS\" data-anker=\"Z30a31b111175e0ac68095e551b8056af\" data-section-id=\"b8cHOV0\" data-sememe-id=\"sIXtVz\">glans penis</a> are expected 3 hours after this procedure. Moreover, wound infection at the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=rF0fj3&anker=Z67ce853a61229ff007038c97630cd26d\" data-learningcard-id=\"rF0fj3\" data-anker=\"Z67ce853a61229ff007038c97630cd26d\" data-sememe-id=\"6V1jvf0\">circumcision</a> site is most commonly seen 2–3 days after the procedure and typically resolves with the application of triple <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Z4660f53b2b0c85aa3f9ab01bdf3f14f3\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Z4660f53b2b0c85aa3f9ab01bdf3f14f3\">antibiotic</a> ointment (i.e., <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Z37ca24e10ca3a6835fd4b232402957e6\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Z37ca24e10ca3a6835fd4b232402957e6\" data-section-id=\"djcozX0\" data-sememe-id=\"OyXI200\">bacitracin</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Z742ef08d0eccb9457bdf9502cf39a319\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Z742ef08d0eccb9457bdf9502cf39a319\" data-section-id=\"hjccZc0\" data-sememe-id=\"1bb2sH\">neomycin</a>, and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Zf4d22497b81f99faf332279c78d63915\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Zf4d22497b81f99faf332279c78d63915\" data-section-id=\"fPckVc0\" data-sememe-id=\"VbbGsH\">polymyxin</a> B); systemic <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Z4660f53b2b0c85aa3f9ab01bdf3f14f3\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Z4660f53b2b0c85aa3f9ab01bdf3f14f3\">antibiotics</a> are only necessary in rare cases of severe infection.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>F) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=c50aQg&anker=Z81eb7fc28b5ad01c5c85c93702a59588\" data-learningcard-id=\"c50aQg\" data-anker=\"Z81eb7fc28b5ad01c5c85c93702a59588\" data-section-id=\"MyXMf00\" data-sememe-id=\"qBbCbw\">Urinary catheterization</a> is considered in patients with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=550ikg&anker=Za6144db4f72b8bf820f97100f15772ac\" data-learningcard-id=\"550ikg\" data-anker=\"Za6144db4f72b8bf820f97100f15772ac\" data-section-id=\"mNcVb10\" data-sememe-id=\"X3b9St\">postoperative urinary retention</a>. This <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=a40Q3T&anker=Z6f0fa51eb81a7d03aa179eab82aacab8\" data-learningcard-id=\"a40Q3T\" data-anker=\"Z6f0fa51eb81a7d03aa179eab82aacab8\" data-sememe-id=\"-m0DRg\">neonate</a>, however, presents with a wet diaper.</div>",
      "hint": "This neonate's crying, facial grimacing, increased muscle tone, mild tachycardia, tachypnea, and poor feeding after an invasive procedure are most likely physiological and behavioral responses to pain.",
