    {
      "text": "A 2-day-old male newborn is brought to the clinic for a routine exam. The urethral opening is on the ventral aspect of the penis near the coronal margin, and the foreskin is dorsally hooded. The parents request routine circumcision before hospital discharge. Physical examination is otherwise normal, and vital signs are within normal limits.\nWhich of the following is the most appropriate next step in management?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Renal ultrasound"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Dorsal slit procedure"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Refer to a pediatric surgical specialist"
        },
        {
          "id": 4,
          "text": "Proceed with immediate circumcision"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 3,
      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<span data-sememe-id=\"pGWLZM0\">Renal ultrasound</span> is considered in <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Mi0MHf&anker=Z3062e909354f6b056b032a9fa3c96197\" data-learningcard-id=\"Mi0MHf\" data-anker=\"Z3062e909354f6b056b032a9fa3c96197\" data-section-id=\"c7Xakz\" data-sememe-id=\"mIaVWN\">hypospadias</a> with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xo0EVS&anker=Z3538c7d0d3c09a64652ecccc7971d5ae\" data-learningcard-id=\"xo0EVS\" data-anker=\"Z3538c7d0d3c09a64652ecccc7971d5ae\" data-section-id=\"h_ccLU0\">proximal</a> urethral openings or ambiguous genitalia due to potential urogenital anomalies. This case involves isolated <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xo0EVS&anker=Zce232f978ea5a8fb9edbb980a41502b8\" data-learningcard-id=\"xo0EVS\" data-anker=\"Zce232f978ea5a8fb9edbb980a41502b8\" data-section-id=\"h_ccLU0\">distal</a> <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Mi0MHf&anker=Z3062e909354f6b056b032a9fa3c96197\" data-learningcard-id=\"Mi0MHf\" data-anker=\"Z3062e909354f6b056b032a9fa3c96197\" data-section-id=\"c7Xakz\" data-sememe-id=\"mIaVWN\">hypospadias</a>, with minimal risk of renal anomalies, making <span data-sememe-id=\"pGWLZM0\">renal ultrasound</span> unnecessary.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) INCORRECT:</h4>A <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=oi00sf&anker=Zae0bd254b97cb9e360c1c09da1d49ad3\" data-learningcard-id=\"oi00sf\" data-anker=\"Zae0bd254b97cb9e360c1c09da1d49ad3\" data-section-id=\"tMcXq10\" data-sememe-id=\"vZ1AW20\">dorsal slit</a> procedure addresses <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=oi00sf&anker=Z423891b0faa1bd883c88dbfaf1e22b6d\" data-learningcard-id=\"oi00sf\" data-anker=\"Z423891b0faa1bd883c88dbfaf1e22b6d\" data-section-id=\"GMcBJ10\" data-sememe-id=\"Cl0q_T\">phimosis</a> by incising the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=l60vOS&anker=Zb327ac90601ec5904ca8e539cba62638\" data-learningcard-id=\"l60vOS\" data-anker=\"Zb327ac90601ec5904ca8e539cba62638\" data-section-id=\"b8cHOV0\" data-sememe-id=\"yycd3U0\">foreskin</a>. In <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Mi0MHf&anker=Z3062e909354f6b056b032a9fa3c96197\" data-learningcard-id=\"Mi0MHf\" data-anker=\"Z3062e909354f6b056b032a9fa3c96197\" data-section-id=\"c7Xakz\" data-sememe-id=\"mIaVWN\">hypospadias</a>, the concern is the misplaced urethral meatus, not a tight <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=l60vOS&anker=Zb327ac90601ec5904ca8e539cba62638\" data-learningcard-id=\"l60vOS\" data-anker=\"Zb327ac90601ec5904ca8e539cba62638\" data-section-id=\"b8cHOV0\" data-sememe-id=\"yycd3U0\">foreskin</a>. The <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=l60vOS&anker=Zb327ac90601ec5904ca8e539cba62638\" data-learningcard-id=\"l60vOS\" data-anker=\"Zb327ac90601ec5904ca8e539cba62638\" data-section-id=\"b8cHOV0\" data-sememe-id=\"yycd3U0\">foreskin</a> is valuable for future repair, so a <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=oi00sf&anker=Zae0bd254b97cb9e360c1c09da1d49ad3\" data-learningcard-id=\"oi00sf\" data-anker=\"Zae0bd254b97cb9e360c1c09da1d49ad3\" data-section-id=\"tMcXq10\" data-sememe-id=\"vZ1AW20\">dorsal slit</a> is inappropriate.</div><div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) CORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Mi0MHf&anker=Z3062e909354f6b056b032a9fa3c96197\" data-learningcard-id=\"Mi0MHf\" data-anker=\"Z3062e909354f6b056b032a9fa3c96197\" data-section-id=\"c7Xakz\" data-sememe-id=\"mIaVWN\">Hypospadias</a> is characterized by a ventrally displaced urethral meatus and a dorsally hooded <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=l60vOS&anker=Zb327ac90601ec5904ca8e539cba62638\" data-learningcard-id=\"l60vOS\" data-anker=\"Zb327ac90601ec5904ca8e539cba62638\" data-section-id=\"b8cHOV0\" data-sememe-id=\"yycd3U0\">foreskin</a> due to incomplete <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xo0EVS&anker=Zb18ada80aa42846bdf8d3785e2480ff1\" data-learningcard-id=\"xo0EVS\" data-anker=\"Zb18ada80aa42846bdf8d3785e2480ff1\" data-section-id=\"h_ccLU0\">ventral</a> <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=l60vOS&anker=Zb327ac90601ec5904ca8e539cba62638\" data-learningcard-id=\"l60vOS\" data-anker=\"Zb327ac90601ec5904ca8e539cba62638\" data-section-id=\"b8cHOV0\" data-sememe-id=\"yycd3U0\">foreskin</a> development. The urethral opening near the coronal margin confirms <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Mi0MHf&anker=Z3062e909354f6b056b032a9fa3c96197\" data-learningcard-id=\"Mi0MHf\" data-anker=\"Z3062e909354f6b056b032a9fa3c96197\" data-section-id=\"c7Xakz\" data-sememe-id=\"mIaVWN\">hypospadias</a>. Surgical repair, ideally between 6 and 18 months, corrects the urethral position and any associated <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Mi0MHf&anker=Z67e203a289b75366104d92875382747d\" data-learningcard-id=\"Mi0MHf\" data-anker=\"Z67e203a289b75366104d92875382747d\" data-section-id=\"c7Xakz\" data-sememe-id=\"bBcHze0\">chordee</a>. Early referral to a pediatric surgical specialist is crucial for evaluation, counseling, and preserving <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=l60vOS&anker=Zb327ac90601ec5904ca8e539cba62638\" data-learningcard-id=\"l60vOS\" data-anker=\"Zb327ac90601ec5904ca8e539cba62638\" data-section-id=\"b8cHOV0\" data-sememe-id=\"yycd3U0\">foreskin</a> tissue for reconstruction, optimizing cosmetic and functional outcomes.<br><br><span class=\"wichtig\"><b>Key learning point: </b></span>In cases of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Mi0MHf&anker=Z3062e909354f6b056b032a9fa3c96197\" data-learningcard-id=\"Mi0MHf\" data-anker=\"Z3062e909354f6b056b032a9fa3c96197\" data-section-id=\"c7Xakz\" data-sememe-id=\"mIaVWN\">hypospadias</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=rF0fj3&anker=Z67ce853a61229ff007038c97630cd26d\" data-learningcard-id=\"rF0fj3\" data-anker=\"Z67ce853a61229ff007038c97630cd26d\" data-sememe-id=\"6V1jvf0\">circumcision</a> should be avoided and the patient should be referred to a pediatric <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=7I04Vh&anker=Z449c383ee1ad9fd4aa9f2bba4d37881e\" data-learningcard-id=\"7I04Vh\" data-anker=\"Z449c383ee1ad9fd4aa9f2bba4d37881e\" data-section-id=\"w41hlS0\">surgeon</a> for evaluation and potential surgical repair.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) INCORRECT:</h4>In <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Mi0MHf&anker=Z3062e909354f6b056b032a9fa3c96197\" data-learningcard-id=\"Mi0MHf\" data-anker=\"Z3062e909354f6b056b032a9fa3c96197\" data-section-id=\"c7Xakz\" data-sememe-id=\"mIaVWN\">hypospadias</a>, the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=l60vOS&anker=Zb327ac90601ec5904ca8e539cba62638\" data-learningcard-id=\"l60vOS\" data-anker=\"Zb327ac90601ec5904ca8e539cba62638\" data-section-id=\"b8cHOV0\" data-sememe-id=\"yycd3U0\">foreskin</a> is valuable for future reconstructive <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=7I04Vh&anker=Za68e01313423572283ce418087f356cb\" data-learningcard-id=\"7I04Vh\" data-anker=\"Za68e01313423572283ce418087f356cb\" data-section-id=\"w41hlS0\">surgery</a>. Immediate <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=rF0fj3&anker=Z67ce853a61229ff007038c97630cd26d\" data-learningcard-id=\"rF0fj3\" data-anker=\"Z67ce853a61229ff007038c97630cd26d\" data-sememe-id=\"6V1jvf0\">circumcision</a> would remove this tissue, eliminating an important option for surgical repair, which often relies on local tissue to achieve optimal functional and cosmetic outcomes.</div>",
